1322
01:25:57,390 --> 01:25:59,072
Somebody brought you to church and you said


1323
01:25:59,072 --> 01:25:59,873
I've been in pain.


1324
01:26:01,173 --> 01:26:03,434
You need forgiveness.


1325
01:26:03,434 --> 01:26:04,755
I'm not saying join a church.


1326
01:26:04,755 --> 01:26:06,336
It's not good people that go to heaven


1327
01:26:06,336 --> 01:26:07,937
and bad people that go to hell.


1328
01:26:07,937 --> 01:26:09,418
It's forgiven people.


1329
01:26:09,418 --> 01:26:12,179
It's sinners that cry out to a holy Savior.


1330
01:26:12,179 --> 01:26:13,580
Say, Pastor, this morning


1331
01:26:13,580 --> 01:26:15,041
I need to be forgiven.


1332
01:26:15,041 --> 01:26:16,322
I need Jesus.


1333
01:26:16,322 --> 01:26:18,083
Raise up your hand all through the auditorium.


1334
01:26:18,083 --> 01:26:19,503
I need to be born again.


1335
01:26:19,503 --> 01:26:20,284
I need to be saved.


1336
01:26:20,284 --> 01:26:21,204
A number of hands.


1337
01:26:21,204 --> 01:26:22,925
Hallelujah.


1338
01:26:22,925 --> 01:26:25,347
Maybe that's why you're here.


1339
01:26:25,347 --> 01:26:27,368
You've been trying to process the pain.


1340
01:26:27,368 --> 01:26:29,129
And the answer is as simple as Jesus.


1341
01:26:30,641 --> 01:26:31,982
Those of you with your hands raised


1342
01:26:31,982 --> 01:26:35,165
I want you to pray with me in the quietness of your heart.


1343
01:26:35,165 --> 01:26:37,286
Say, Dear God, I know that I am a sinner.


1344
01:26:37,286 --> 01:26:41,189
I believe Jesus Christ died for my sin.


1345
01:26:41,189 --> 01:26:44,452
And this morning I repent of my sin


1346
01:26:44,452 --> 01:26:49,556
and I accept Jesus Christ as my Savior.


1347
01:26:50,577 --> 01:26:52,058
In Jesus' name, Amen.


1348
01:26:53,199 --> 01:26:55,080
We're going to sing a closing hymn.


1349
01:26:55,080 --> 01:26:56,722
It's called Just As I Am.


1350
01:26:57,743 --> 01:26:59,323
It's a hymn that I always close


1351
01:26:59,323 --> 01:27:02,444
when I close a service at the mission.


1352
01:27:02,444 --> 01:27:03,045
But if you're here


1353
01:27:03,045 --> 01:27:03,745
why don't we all stand


1354
01:27:03,745 --> 01:27:04,965
and we'll sing this together.


1355
01:27:04,965 --> 01:27:07,526
The front is open here.


1356
01:27:07,526 --> 01:27:10,307
Again, hear me this morning.


1357
01:27:11,347 --> 01:27:13,107
So we just don't play church.


1358
01:27:13,107 --> 01:27:15,048
We walk out the door.


1359
01:27:15,048 --> 01:27:16,908
Some of you were spoken to this morning.


1360
01:27:18,189 --> 01:27:18,989
You know who you are.


1361
01:27:18,989 --> 01:27:20,109
God spoke to your heart.


1362
01:27:20,109 --> 01:27:22,210
You need to let it go.


1363
01:27:22,210 --> 01:27:25,131
And as we sing this song


1364
01:27:25,131 --> 01:27:27,137
just as I am


1365
01:27:27,137 --> 01:27:31,022
Why don't you come down here, pray with somebody, come to the altar.


1366
01:27:31,022 --> 01:27:32,924
This is your time.


1367
01:27:32,924 --> 01:27:35,487
The devil has had a field day with you.


1368
01:27:35,487 --> 01:27:40,933
And what you need to do, let it go.


1369
01:27:40,933 --> 01:27:43,156
So why don't you come on down, let's sing.


1370
01:27:47,186 --> 01:27:53,011
Why don't you come down today?


1371
01:27:53,011 --> 01:27:58,696
Come on down, come on down.


1372
01:27:58,696 --> 01:28:02,820
You know God has spoken to your heart this morning.


1373
01:28:02,820 --> 01:28:03,981
Hallelujah, hallelujah.


1374
01:28:03,981 --> 01:28:07,084
It is time this morning, hallelujah.


1375
01:28:07,084 --> 01:28:09,106
Come on down, come on down.


1376
01:28:10,200 --> 01:28:13,062
You've lived with the pain for too long.


1377
01:28:13,062 --> 01:28:16,445
You don't know how to process what happened to you.


1378
01:28:16,445 --> 01:28:17,346
You struggle.


1379
01:28:17,346 --> 01:28:19,948
I want to tell you there's a God who loves you.


1380
01:28:19,948 --> 01:28:23,931
There's a Savior who shed His blood for you.


1381
01:28:23,931 --> 01:28:26,052
Hallelujah.


1382
01:28:26,052 --> 01:28:28,614
Come on down.


1383
01:28:32,477 --> 01:28:33,658
Anybody else tonight?


1384
01:28:33,658 --> 01:28:34,419
Come on down.


1385
01:28:37,342 --> 01:28:41,185
Just as I am, day and night.


1386
01:28:41,185 --> 01:28:44,127
Maybe some of the balcony


1387
01:28:44,127 --> 01:28:47,549
maybe you're wrestling with it.


1388
01:28:47,549 --> 01:28:51,131
Why don't you come to Jesus today?


1389
01:28:51,131 --> 01:28:54,254
Come on down, come on down.


1390
01:28:54,254 --> 01:29:00,638
My soul, I want my life to be.


1391
01:29:05,785 --> 01:29:14,590
Come on, others coming down.


1392
01:29:17,212 --> 01:29:30,600
I'm going to have a prayer for everybody after the word.


1393
01:29:33,101 --> 01:29:36,624
And I want you to come if there's others who are struggling.


1394
01:29:36,624 --> 01:29:38,125
This is your moment.


1395
01:29:38,125 --> 01:29:39,266
This is your time.


1396
01:29:39,266 --> 01:29:45,211
You've held on to it too long.


1397
01:29:45,211 --> 01:29:47,934
Time to let it go.


1398
01:29:47,934 --> 01:29:48,194
Let it go.


1399
01:30:07,117 --> 01:30:13,061
I come, I come.


1400
01:30:16,745 --> 01:30:19,126
Let me pray for those that are down here.


1401
01:30:19,126 --> 01:30:20,987
When I look at those that are here


1402
01:30:20,987 --> 01:30:22,228
there's a lot of pain that's here.


1403
01:30:23,709 --> 01:30:25,730
There's a lot of uncertainty.


1404
01:30:25,730 --> 01:30:27,010
But I want to tell you this morning


1405
01:30:27,010 --> 01:30:28,971
there's a Savior that can heal.


1406
01:30:28,971 --> 01:30:31,553
Let the healing process begin today.


1407
01:30:31,553 --> 01:30:35,074
It might not be instantaneous


1408
01:30:35,074 --> 01:30:36,195
but you took the first step.


1409
01:30:36,195 --> 01:30:37,496
Let me pray.


1410
01:30:37,496 --> 01:30:38,976
Father, I pray for every man


1411
01:30:38,976 --> 01:30:40,057
and woman that's before me.


1412
01:30:41,501 --> 01:30:43,742
God, you know their hearts and you know what they've been through.


1413
01:30:43,742 --> 01:30:45,382
You know the healing that they need.


1414
01:30:45,382 --> 01:30:50,983
And I pray tonight that you would give them the supernatural strength


1415
01:30:52,244 --> 01:30:59,426
to go to bed for the first time in years not angry with that issue gone.


1416
01:30:59,426 --> 01:31:02,726
Because you told us from our hearts to forgive.


1417
01:31:02,726 --> 01:31:04,987
You know the issues, pain.


1418
01:31:04,987 --> 01:31:05,847
Bless those.


1419
01:31:05,847 --> 01:31:06,427
Guide those.


1420
01:31:06,427 --> 01:31:07,608
Give them your strength.


1421
01:31:07,608 --> 01:31:08,988
I pray for each and every one.


1422
01:31:09,999 --> 01:31:11,759
In Jesus' name I pray.


1423
01:31:11,759 --> 01:31:13,960
Amen, amen, and amen.


1424
01:31:13,960 --> 01:31:15,800
Amen, Pastor.


1425
01:31:15,800 --> 01:31:16,320
You know what?


1426
01:31:17,621 --> 01:31:21,342
That hymn is so beautiful, isn't it?


1427
01:31:21,342 --> 01:31:22,122
Just as I am.


1428
01:31:22,122 --> 01:31:23,222
Did you hear those words?


1429
01:31:23,222 --> 01:31:24,522
Go to the first verse.


1430
01:31:24,522 --> 01:31:27,623
Let's close the meeting by singing that hymn.


1431
01:31:27,623 --> 01:31:28,263
Listen.


1432
01:31:28,263 --> 01:31:32,904
As I am, without one plea, no excuses.


1433
01:31:32,904 --> 01:31:34,005
I've been wrong


1434
01:31:34,005 --> 01:31:36,720
but that thy blood was shed for me.


1435
01:31:36,720 --> 01:31:37,881
That's my only hope


1436
01:31:37,881 --> 01:31:39,183
is what you can do for me


1437
01:31:39,183 --> 01:31:41,365
not what I can do for you.


1438
01:31:41,365 --> 01:31:44,569
Let's sing it in closing, shall we?


1439
01:31:44,569 --> 01:31:44,910
Amen?


1440
01:31:54,621 --> 01:31:55,182
Here we go, sing.


1441
01:31:56,797 --> 01:32:08,366
Just as I am without one plea


1442
01:32:08,366 --> 01:32:12,550
but that Thy blood


1443
01:32:13,791 --> 01:32:17,814
it was shed on me


1444
01:32:19,515 --> 01:32:31,468
and that Thy I come to thee


1445
01:32:31,468 --> 01:32:43,655
O Lamb of God, I come, I come.


1446
01:32:44,655 --> 01:32:46,597
Lord, we ask for all of us


1447
01:32:46,597 --> 01:32:47,817
especially here in the front


1448
01:32:47,817 --> 01:32:50,159
give us today the spirit of a lamb.


1449
01:32:51,980 --> 01:32:55,130
We follow Jesus, who was the Lamb of God.


1450
01:32:55,130 --> 01:33:00,514
Not angry, not yelling, not screaming, not holding on to stuff.


1451
01:33:00,514 --> 01:33:01,855
He even prayed, Lord


1452
01:33:01,855 --> 01:33:04,458
you prayed for those who crucified you.


1453
01:33:04,458 --> 01:33:05,979
We cannot do that.


1454
01:33:05,979 --> 01:33:08,701
You have to give us the grace to do that.


1455
01:33:08,701 --> 01:33:13,625
But we let it go today in Jesus' name.


1456
01:33:13,625 --> 01:33:17,388
We're not going to let those tormentors torment us again.


1457
01:33:17,388 --> 01:33:18,929
It's in your hands now, God.


1458
01:33:20,090 --> 01:33:21,932
Thank you for everyone who's here.


1459
01:33:21,932 --> 01:33:23,653
Thank you for everything that's happened.


1460
01:33:24,990 --> 01:33:28,393
Thank you for Pastor Phillip being here and being such a blessing.


1461
01:33:28,393 --> 01:33:31,956
You've given us a beautiful day, those little babies.


1462
01:33:31,956 --> 01:33:37,780
Just bless the offering now, the fellowship with the 40s, the downstairs with the first timers.


1463
01:33:37,780 --> 01:33:39,502
Just give us a beautiful end


1464
01:33:39,502 --> 01:33:41,703
we pray in Jesus' name.


1465
01:33:41,703 --> 01:33:45,566
And everyone said, turn around and hug somebody.


1466
01:33:45,566 --> 01:33:47,908
Give someone a hug and a handshake.


1467
01:33:47,908 --> 01:33:49,930
My choir is going to sing one more time.